PRIVACY POLICY
Introduction
​
Joymatiq develops and publishes games for mobile devices. This privacy policy describes how Joymatiq (also referred to as "we", "us" or "our") and its third-party partners collect, store, use and share information about you. This Privacy Policy applies to all of our games, website (
https://www.joymatiq.com
) and any other service that we may offer (collectively referred to as "Services"). By downloading and/or playing our games, or interacting with our website or other Services, you agree to the collection and use of your information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. If you have any concerns about the use of your information as described in this Privacy Policy, please refrain from playing our games, interacting with our website and other Services.
​
Playing our games
​
Our games are intended for amusement purposes only. Our games do not offer 'real money gambling' or an opportunity to win real money or prizes. Our games are strictly intended for players 21 years or older.
​
Our games collect, store and use only game related data locally on your device(s). Our games do not collect, store, use or share any information about you. However, our games use third-party services that enable game development, provide additional content and experiences. These third-party services include:
​
Solar2D
​
Our games are built using Solar2D, a cross-platform app development framework.
Solar2D
may collect information such as your device IP address, device operating system, device specific identifier as well as information related to your game sessions. We recommend that you review
Solar2D
's
Privacy Policy which can be found
here
. Since our games are built entirely using
Solar2D
, you will not be able to opt out of this service. If you have any concerns about the use of your information as described in
Solar2D's
Privacy Policy, please refrain from playing our games altogether.
​
Flurry
​
Our games incorporate Flurry Analytics, a mobile analytics framework. This provides us a platform for analyzing your interactions with our games so that we may better understand the performance of our games. This analytical process enables us to troubleshoot, improve and optimize our games with future updates so that you may have the best possible player experience. In this regard, Flurry may collect information such as your device IP address, device operating system, device settings, device specific identifier, mobile network as well as information related to your game sessions. We recommend that you review Flurry's Privacy Policy which can be found
here
. You can opt out of this service at any time by disabling the 'Analytics Sharing' option in the game's settings.
​
Unity
Ads
​
Our games incorporate Unity Ads, an in-app video advertising framework, that enables us to serve rewarded video ads to you in exchange for virtual currency. With the intention of serving video ads that are more relevant to you, Unity Ads may collect information such as your device IP address, device specific identifier, advertising identifier as well as information related to your demography and interests. We recommend that you review Unity Ads' Privacy Policy which can be found
here
. You can opt out of providing information to this service at any time by enabling the 'Limit Ad Tracking' option in your device settings (Settings > Privacy > Advertising > Limit Ad Tracking). Even if you limit ad tracking, video ads will still be served to you when you request for them specifically, but Unity Ads will no longer be able to use your personal information to serve you with more relevant ads.
​
Visiting our w
ebsite
​
When you visit our website, we do not collect, store, use or share any information about you. In the event that you contact us, we may keep a record of that correspondence. However, our website is built entirely using a third-party website development service:
​
Wix
​
Wix may collect information such as your device specifications, device operating system, internet browser, internet service provider, language settings, keyboard settings, cookies as well as information related to your browsing sessions. We recommend that you review Wix's Privacy Policy which can be found
here
.
​
Third‑party websites
​
Our games, website and other Services may contain links to third-party websites. Information collected by such third-party websites are governed by their privacy practices. We encourage you to learn about the privacy practices of those third-party websites.
​
Privacy questions
​
If you have any questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy, please
contact us
.
​
Changes to our Privacy Policy
​
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time and we will publish the updated Privacy Policy on this web page. The updated Privacy Policy will be effective from the date of publishing. Please review this web page periodically for any changes.
This Privacy Policy was last updated on November 03, 2023.